<% content_for :title, "Analytics" %>

<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-3">
  <div>
    <h1 class="h3 mb-1">Analytics</h1>
    <div class="text-muted small">
      <% if current_user.tenant %>
        All-time scope, <%= current_user.tenant.name %> · <%= pluralize(@analytics.total_proposals, "proposal") %>.
      <% else %>
        No tenant assigned to your account — analytics are empty until you're invited into one.
      <% end %>
      Per PRD-07 §6, a date / location / job-type filter bar lives here once those scopes are wired.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "analytics/dashboard", analytics: @analytics %>

<%# --- Pending data callout ------------------------------------------ %>
<div class="card border-warning shadow-sm">
  <div class="card-header bg-warning-subtle">
    <h2 class="h6 mb-0">Pending data — what's needed to fully realize PRD-07</h2>
  </div>
  <ul class="list-group list-group-flush small">
    <li class="list-group-item">
      <strong>Inbound-message store.</strong> No table records customer replies today. Blocks: <em>Avg Time to First Reply</em> tile · <em>Customer Replied</em> funnel stage · <em>Operator Responded</em> funnel stage · <em>Reply Rate</em> originator column.
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item">
      <strong>Operator-reply tracking.</strong> Same inbound store, but for messages your team types in Gmail directly — needed to distinguish a system-sent follow-up from a hand-typed one.
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item">
      <strong>Date / location / job-type filter bar (PRD §6).</strong> Once the filter bar lands, this page will scope to whatever range you pick instead of all-time.
    </li>
    <li class="list-group-item">
      <strong>Period-over-period deltas (PRD §7.1).</strong> Each tile will gain a "X% vs prior period" caption once date filtering is in.
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
